		<h1>Sunset Boulevard</h1>
		<h2>By Aman Kumar</h2>

		<div class="image-container">
			
			<p class="film-content">
						Sunset Boulevard is a widely acclaimed classic of American cinema. This black comedy/film noir follows Joe Gillis, a writer in Hollywood who is struggling to make ends meet. After a car chase, caused by running away from his financial troubles, Joe accidentally stumbles upon the mansion of Norma Desmond, an aging actress from the era of silent films. Learning that Joe is a writer, Norma sees a chance back into the spotlight. However, her obsession with fame leads Joe into a bizarre, dangerous, and tragic adventure. This film is Wilder’s sharp critique of Hollywood and the entertainment industry in general. Its examination of the writers of Hollywood, and obsession with fame are very relevant to this day. 

</p>
<img src="images/sunset.jpg" width="400">
